default&#xa0;defaultCommissioning Academydefault&#xa0;
defaultThe Commissioning Academy brings together senior commissioners from across the public sector to learn from the example of the most successful commissioning organisations – developing a growing cadre of professionals skilled in best practice. 
default&#xa0;
defaultFollowing two pilot programmes, the Commissionin
defaultg Academy was formally launched 
defaultin January 2013 and 
defaultdemand for places has been high. O
defaultf the 114 participants across 
defaultthe 
defaultpilots and first wave, 
defaultover 58% (
default67
default)
default were from Local Authorities.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 8 day programme includes a ‘provider perspective’, where conversations with different types of providers, including SMEs, help the participants gain a greater understanding of opportunities that are being missed to ensure we get the best outcomes possible for tax payers, communities and society as a whole.
